Building user_resv_mem module:
==============================

Prerequisites
-------------
The specific kernel source directory against which the driver
compilation is required must be compiled.

Build
------
$ cd user_resv_mem
$ make KSRC=/path/to/custom/kernel/source

The .ko file will be generated, which can be loaded using:
$ insmod user_resv_mem.ko

Module Params:
$ cache_policy "wc, wb, wt"
	- wc: WRITE_COMBINE
	- wb: WRITE_BACK
	- wt: WRITE_THROUGH
	default is wc
$ chunk_size <memory in bytes>
	- Memory will be allocated to user in chunks.
	default is size of total available memory.
Clean
------
To clean the build directory, the following command can be run:

$ cd user_resv_mem
$ make KSRC=/path/to/custom/kernel/source clean
